# MessKhojo SEO Implementation Plan — Core Content & Technical Tweaks

This plan focuses on immediate SEO improvements for the MessKhojo React SPA (Vite) hosted on Netlify, addressing key items from the audit while deferring sitemaps, robots.txt, and keyword tags as requested.

## User Review Required

Please review the proposed optimizations to titles, descriptions, heading structures, fallback content, and the **District Selection SEO fix**:

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Forced District Modal SEO Impact**: Currently, visiting the base URL `https://messkhojo.com/` without a saved district in `localStorage` forces a full-screen selector modal to open. 
> * **The Issue**: Search engine bots (like Googlebot) crawl with clean state and get blocked by this JS modal, indexing only generic metadata and missing the city-specific listings and pages.
> * **The Fix**: We will add query parameter support (`?district=balasore` / `?district=bhadrak`) to `DistrictProvider`. If a district parameter is present in the URL search params, the modal is automatically bypassed, and the homepage renders city-specific listings and localized metadata.
> * **Static Crawl Paths**: We will list links to these city-specific search URLs (`/?district=balasore` and `/?district=bhadrak`) inside the static fallback `<div id="root">` to ensure Googlebot crawls, indexes, and ranks both city homepages separately.

